correctness.rationale: Several core details are correct (PEALD method, precursors/co-reactant, 100 W plasma, 200 °C, ~1.2 Torr, Si(100) substrate, Type A supercycle In2O3 27 / Ga2O3 1 / ZnO 2, RI=1.93, roughness=0.153 nm, density=6.79 g/cm3, TFT metrics for Type A). However, there are multiple schema and factual issues: (1) Only one process (Type A) is extracted, while the article reports three distinct sequences (Types A, B, C) that should be represented as separate processes. (2) Dosing/purge times are wrong by 10^3 due to using MilliSEC without converting: 0.3 s→300 ms (not 0.3 ms), 25 s→25000 ms (not 25 ms), 10 s→10000 ms (not 10 ms); the co-reactant dosing should reflect 10 s Ar/O2 injection and/or 1 s plasma, not 1 ms. (3) Subthreshold swing unit/value is incorrect: 0.42 V/dec should be reported as 420 mV/dec; 0.42 mV is off by 10^3. (4) Multiple fields violate the schema with null or placeholder values: flowRates.numericValue=None; uniformity.variation.numericValue=None; conformality.aspectRatio.numericValue=None; filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values.quantityValue.numericValue=None; deviceProperties.onOffRatio.numericValue=None; atomicRatio.value set to 'Not Found'; reactor/deliveryMethod/safety set to 'Not Found'. The schema and task disallow nulls/placeholders. (5) thicknessControl.numberofCycles=30 is unsupported (represents one supercycle, not the total cycles used to reach 20 nm) and is not traceable. (6) nucleationPeriod=0 and saturation=True are not reported in the article. (7) materialProperties.electricalProperties.mobility (33.2 cm2/Vs) is taken from TFT device data and duplicates deviceProperties; film-level electrical properties (e.g., Hall) are not provided. These errors and omissions reduce correctness and traceability; the above fields should be corrected or removed, and separate processes for Types A, B, and C should be added with their respective parameters and properties.

completeness.rationale: Major portions of the reported work are missing and several schema violations are present. Key issues: (1) Multiple processes not captured: the article explicitly reports three distinct PEALD IGZO supercycle sequences (Type A, B, C). The extraction includes only one process (Type A). Missing separate processes for Type B and Type C with their own supercycle sequences and properties (Type B: In2O3 13, Ga2O3 1, In2O3 14, ZnO 2; Type C: In2O3 9, Ga2O3 1, In2O3 9, ZnO 1, In2O3 9, ZnO 1). (2) Device metrics missing for Types B and C: the article provides threshold voltage (−1.05 V for B, −1.83 V for C), mobility (14.8 and 20.5 cm2/V·s), and SS (0.31 and 0.23 V/dec). Only Type A values are present. (3) Film properties missing for Types B and C: refractive index (RI increases from 1.93 to 1.96 from A→C), roughness (0.153, 0.146, 0.100 nm for A, B, C), density (6.79→6.53 g/cm3 from A→C), crystallinity trend (Type C approaching amorphous). Only Type A is populated. (4) Composition data incomplete: XRF cation ratios are reported (In increases from 58.7% to 63.5%; Zn decreases from 10% to 6.5%) but not captured; elemental concentration numeric values are set to None and atomicRatio value is ‘Not Found’—both violate schema and traceability. (5) Schema violations with nulls: multiple numericValue fields are None (flowRates for all compounds; uniformity.variation; conformality.aspectRatio; materialProperties.filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values), which are not allowed by the schema (numericValue must be a number). (6) Time unit errors: article gives step times in seconds (0.3 s precursor dose; 25 s purge; 10 s Ar/O2 injection; 1 s plasma exposure; 10 s purge). Extraction uses units of milliseconds without conversion (e.g., 0.3 ms instead of 300 ms; 25 ms instead of 25,000 ms; 10 ms instead of 10,000 ms; 1 ms instead of 1,000 ms), causing 10^3 errors. (7) SS unit mismatch: schema uses millivolts but values are reported in V/dec; the extraction sets 0.42 mV instead of 0.42 V (should be 420 mV if conforming to schema). (8) Unsubstantiated booleans: saturation=True, otherAspects.filmStability=True, reproducibility=True are not explicitly supported by the text and should be omitted or justified. (9) Supercycle design only for Type A; sequences for Types B and C are missing. To improve completeness, add two additional process objects for Types B and C with their correct supercycle sequences, device metrics, film properties (RI, density, roughness, crystallinity), composition (XRF cation ratios), correct time unit conversions, and avoid null numeric values to comply with the schema.
